766
01:21:12,575 --> 01:21:37,122
[SPEAKER_12]: Demonstration by clear and convincing evidence that the vacant commercial property or vacant industrial property cannot reasonably be sold, leased, preoccupied, or otherwise activated due to a bona fide legal dispute concerning title or possessionary rights, including but not limited to administration of an estate where legal authority to convey or lease the property is unresolved, pending probate, land court, or superior

767
01:21:38,208 --> 01:21:42,091
[SPEAKER_12]: Proceedings to quiet, title, or resolve defects in the chain of title.

768
01:21:42,211 --> 01:21:47,195
[SPEAKER_12]: Active litigation concerning ownership, control, or the right to lease or convey the property.

769
01:21:47,835 --> 01:21:54,080
[SPEAKER_12]: Or a court order, injunction, or legal constraint that materially limits the court's ability to act with respect to the property.

770
01:21:54,580 --> 01:22:01,105
[SPEAKER_12]: Any waiver granted under this subsection shall be temporary, shall be subject to periodic review, and shall expire upon resolution.

771
01:22:02,658 --> 01:22:04,979
[SPEAKER_12]: of the underlying legal impediment.

772
01:22:05,079 --> 01:22:24,504
[SPEAKER_12]: So this was essentially just a clarification of the, of one of the exemption, of one of the exemption conditions by, under which a vacant property would be exempted from the annual fees.

