1158
02:02:22,749 --> 02:02:24,150
[SPEAKER_12]: The other.

1159
02:02:25,145 --> 02:02:28,087
[SPEAKER_12]: major one had to do with enforcement.

1160
02:02:28,147 --> 02:02:47,962
[SPEAKER_12]: This was, I believe this was added in at the request of, to address one of Kayla's concerns just about, again, one thing that the staff liked about this is, again, that so much of it was left up to the discretion, so much of the enforcement was left up to the discretion of staff.

1161
02:02:49,803 --> 02:02:59,425
[SPEAKER_12]: And this was sort of meant to clarify the building commissioner's authority in these areas, violations and penalties enforcement.

1162
02:02:59,545 --> 02:03:10,508
[SPEAKER_12]: The building commissioner and other officials responsible for enforcing this section may prioritize inspections and enforcement actions based on available municipal resources and the degree to which a property

1163
02:03:11,448 --> 02:03:15,553
[SPEAKER_12]: presents risks to public health, safety, neighborhood conditions, or municipal services.

1164
02:03:16,194 --> 02:03:26,626
[SPEAKER_12]: In administering the section, the city may also seek voluntary compliance and corrective action by property owners prior to initiating formal enforcement proceedings.

1165
02:03:27,427 --> 02:03:33,489
[SPEAKER_12]: including providing notice, guidance, or reasonable opportunity to remedy conditions or bring property into compliance.

1166
02:03:33,789 --> 02:03:49,795
[SPEAKER_12]: B factors may be considered in prioritizing enforcement include, but are not limited to, the duration of vacancy, evidence of deterioration, unsafe conditions, or nuisance activity complaints from members of the public, prior violations of this section or other applicable laws.

1167
02:03:50,635 --> 02:03:55,359
[SPEAKER_12]: and the degree of cooperation by the owner in addressing vacancy or maintenance concerns.

1168
02:03:55,479 --> 02:04:15,333
[SPEAKER_12]: See nothing in this subsection shall be construed to exempt any property to requirements of this section or to limit the enforcement of the city to the authority of the city to enforce this section with respect to any property when the city determines enforcement is necessary to protect the public health, safety or welfare.

1169
02:04:17,595 --> 02:04:21,659
[SPEAKER_12]: Any comments, questions, concerns, thoughts?

1170
02:04:22,319 --> 02:04:22,920
[SPEAKER_12]: Councillor Sang.

1171
